The paper proposes a new method of parameterizing the initial hidden state of an RNN, which improves performance on an associative retrieval task by conditioning the RNN initial hidden state on contextual information from the input sequence. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), natural language processing (cs.CL), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural networks (cs.NE), and computer vision (cs.CV).
